Monic quadratic polynomials $ P(x)$ and $ Q(x)$ have the property that $ P(Q(x))$ has zeroes at $ x=-23,-21,-17, \text{and} -15$, and $ Q(P(x))$ has zeroes at $ x=-59, -57, -51, \text{and} -49$. What is the sum of the minimum values of $ P(x)$ and $ Q(x)$?\\
\\
$ \textbf{(A)}\ \text{-100} \qquad \textbf{(B)}\ \text{-82} \qquad \textbf{(C)}\ \text{-73} \qquad \textbf{(D)}\ \text{-64} \qquad \textbf{(E)}\ 0$
